- **Problem:** Neither Ethernet port came up on first boot — the base `rk3576.dtsi` has both GMACs `status = "disabled"` and our DTS only declared aliases without overriding the nodes.
- **Fix:** Added complete `&gmac0`, `&gmac1`, `&mdio0`, `&mdio1` node overrides with full configuration reverse-engineered from factory firmware.

### 13. Live Device Investigation (SSH to Factory Firmware)
- Established SSH to the Photonicat 2 running factory firmware at `172.16.0.1` (password `photonicat`).
- Gathered comprehensive live hardware data via SSH:
  - Confirmed model `Ariaboard photonicat2` with compatible `ariaboard,photonicat2`.
  - Confirmed `eth0` = WAN (NO-CARRIER/down), `eth1` = LAN (UP, 1000Mb/s full-duplex, connected to our PC).
