### 21. TTL/HL Mangling (nftables)

Added TTL/Hop-Limit mangling rules to prevent carrier detection of tethered traffic.

**File:** `/etc/nftables.d/90-wwan-ttl.nft`

```nft
chain wwan_ttl_postrouting {
  type filter hook postrouting priority mangle + 1; policy accept;
  oifname "wwan0" ip ttl set 65
  oifname "wwan0" ip6 hoplimit set 65
}
```

Sets outgoing TTL/HL to 65 on the wwan0 interface (appears as 64 to the carrier after one hop — indistinguishable from a single device).

**Note on chain naming:** Uses a dedicated chain name `wwan_ttl_postrouting` with its own hook at `priority mangle + 1`. Do NOT use `chain mangle_postrouting` — that would conflict with fw4's own chain definition (see issue below).

